<p>South Carolina presents an exceptional opportunity for homeowners to harness solar energy and optimize their HVAC systems for maximum efficiency and savings. The Palmetto State enjoys abundant sunshine with an average of 4.9 peak sun hours per day, making it one of the most solar-friendly states in the Southeast. This generous solar resource, combined with electricity rates averaging 12.5¬¢ per kWh, creates compelling economics for residential solar installations. Duke Energy, the state's primary utility provider serving over 750,000 customers, offers net metering programs that allow homeowners to sell excess solar power back to the grid, further enhancing the financial benefits of solar adoption.</p>

