<h2>South Carolina Incentives & Rebates</h2>
<p>South Carolina offers some of the most attractive solar incentives in the Southeast, creating exceptional value for homeowners investing in renewable energy systems. The federal Investment Tax Credit (ITC) provides a 30% tax credit for solar installations through 2032, with no cap on the credit amount. This credit applies to the total system cost including equipment, installation, and permitting fees. For a typical \$20,000 solar installation, the federal credit alone provides \$6,000 in tax savings, significantly reducing the net investment cost.</p>

<p>The state of South Carolina enhances federal incentives with its own solar tax credit program, offering 25% of the installation cost up to \$3,500 or 50% of the taxpayer's state income tax liability, whichever is less. This state credit can be carried forward for up to 10 years if it exceeds the current year's tax liability, ensuring homeowners can capture the full benefit regardless of their annual tax situation. When combined with the federal credit, total tax incentives can reach up to 55% of the system cost, creating compelling economics for solar adoption.</p>

