<p>For HVAC systems, South Carolina participates in federal tax credit programs for high-efficiency heat pumps and Energy Star qualified equipment. The federal tax credit provides up to \$2,000 for qualifying heat pump installations with SEER ratings of 16 or higher and HSPF ratings of 9.0 or higher. Some utility companies offer additional rebates for efficient HVAC equipment, with programs varying by service territory. Duke Energy periodically offers rebates ranging from \$250-\$500 for high-efficiency heat pump installations, smart thermostats, and energy audits.</p>

